<br><br>
***<br>
Just noticed that there should be 2 Phrups listed, not 1.<br>
***<br>
<br><br>
After seeing Andrew&#39;s tournament report, I knew I had to build a version of his deck. I immediately dropped the Bog Wellisks, 2 of the Hurricane Orishes (I _love_ that creature, but I had to drop something), a Phrup, & the Hunter Jile (not much Core in my area). After playtesting, I discovered that the 3rd Parathin is unnecessary and will sometime clog your hand, as is the 2nd Tidal Wave. I replaced one of the Stone Storms with a 3rd Thunderquake, and took his advice by swapping the Storm of Fishes for a Riptide. The Beams of Light were replaced with a Spellpulse and a Relic Stalker, but I am thinking about adding one of the Beams back instead of the Spellpulse - jury&#39;s still out on that one.<br>
<br><br>
There were several relics I saw that the deck needed: adding Rayje&#39;s Sword meant that burrowed creatures or Bograth&#39;s anti-damage cards were no longer a problem, and the Orothean Goggles allowed me to cycle my deck faster, which is VERY important when interchanging back to O&#39;Qua. Nalo became another answer to weenie swarms, especially since I added 2 Warrior&#39;s Boots. (Boots also allow me to play creatures on M&#39;Rika while in my 2nd p/s/r/ step, which can allow me to interchange on her when I normally couldn&#39;t.)<br>
<br><br>
My favorite addition to the deck is one I used to great amusement in my Shimmer deck - Drought. Since it only affects cards in play when the Drought is cast, any magi I interchange into after casting it is unaffected.<br>
<br><br>
Any questions/comments are greatly appreciated.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
